# OOP design

Naming follows [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md).

## Tell, Don't Ask

**Tell:** call an intent method (`connect`, `subscribe`, `processConnect`) that owns the decision.

**Don't ask:** avoid `if (session.getStatus() == X) { session.setStatus(Y); … }` spread across callers.

```
StompClient API  →  StompClientImpl  →  Transport / Stomp protocol
StompServer      →  Session          →  MessageHandler / SubscriptionHandler
```

- **Public API:** thin facade; delegate to implementation.
- **Session / StompClientImpl:** own connection state machine and frame handling.
- **Handlers:** callbacks; server tells `MessageHandler.process`, not raw frame parsing in handlers.

```java
// ❌ Caller owns CONNECT transition
if (status == Status.STARTED) { status = Status.CONNECTED; channel.write(connectedFrame); }

// ✅ Session owns the transition
session.processConnect(message);
```

Apply on **new or touched** behaviour; consolidate legacy ask-then-set in the same change.

## Law of Demeter

Call only on self, objects you create, parameters, and **direct** components — not on objects returned by those calls.

```java
// ❌ train wreck
if (client.getTransport().getListener().isConnected()) { … }

// ✅
if (client.isConnected()) { … }
```

| Layer | Rule |
|-------|------|
| Public API | No reaching into `internal` from outside the module |
| Session / StompClientImpl | Expose `isConnected()`, `getProtocolVersion()` instead of deep graphs |
| Handlers | Receive only what they need (`topic`, `body`, `OutboundChannel`) |

Allowed: one direct step — `message.headers().get(Header.DESTINATION)`.

## No method bypass

A **bypass** forwards the same arguments with no added behaviour. Call the target directly.

```java
// ❌ bypass chain
public void foo(X x) { helper.foo(x); }  // helper only forwards

// ✅ intentional public factory
StompClient.create(url) → StompClientImpl.create(url)
```

| Allowed wrapper | Bypass |
|-----------------|--------|
| Public API hiding internal types | `helper.create(url)` → `StompClient.create(url)` with no logic |
| Validation, mapping, SPI contract | Same-args pass-through to callee |

## Never

- Duplicate state-check + mutation in multiple callers.
- Parse STOMP frames in handler callbacks when `Session` should own protocol logic.
- Copy the same getter chain into a second class — extract on the owning type.
